AB We use laboratory experiments to explore merger failure due to
   conflicting organizational cultures. We introduce a laboratory paradigm
   for studying organizational culture that captures several key elements
   of the phenomenon. In our experiments, we allow subjects in "firms" to
   develop a culture, and then merge two firms. As, expected, performance
   decreases following the merging of two laboratory firms. In addition,
   subjects overestimate the performance of the merged firm and attribute
   the decrease in performance to members of the other firm rather than to
   situational difficulties created by conflicting culture.
