   cycle. Organizational inertia influences the rapidity with which the
   infrastructure activities benefit from higher product quality,
   especially for the more specialized activities. Finally, our findings
   suggest that although the savings in infrastructure from quality
   improvement are substantial, there are diminishing returns to quality
   improvement in infrastructure activities.
