   which can result in time-consuming searches that provide redundant or
   dominated alternatives. Our research demonstrates analytically how
   shopbot designs can be improved by developing a utility model of
   consumer purchasing behavior. This utility model considers the intrinsic
   value of the product and its attributes, the disutility from waiting,
