   higher price than the other and sells less today, in the future the firm
   can benefit from the other firm's larger reduction in available capacity
   through rewards. Thus, reward programs also provide additional
   incentives for firms to set higher current prices. Finally, since reward
   programs can add flexibility in adjusting the available capacities to
   the market demand, firms increase the size of regular capacities with
   reward programs.
