   unforeseeable uncertainty and complexity: trial and error learning and
   selectionism. Trial and error learning involves a flexible (unplanned)
   adjustment of the considered actions and targets to new information
   about the relevant environment as it emerges. Selectionism involves
   pursuing several approaches independently of one another and picking the
   best one ex post.
