   in a laboratory setting using a novel multistage trust game where social
   gains are achieved if players trust each other in each stage. In each
   stage, also, players have an opportunity to appropriate these gains or
   be trustworthy by sharing them. Players are strangers because they do
   not know the identity of others and, they will not play them again.
   Thus, there is no prospect of future interaction to induce trusting
   behavior, and, we study the trust-building process where there is little
   scope for social relations and networks.
