   goods manufacturer faces a trade-off between leasing, which commits the
   manufacturer to not overproduce, and selling, which commits it to not
   underproduce. Our contribution is to identify this trade-off and show
   how a durable goods manufacturer can use a combination of leasing and
   selling to balance its strategic commitment across both its own market
